net.heroicefforts.viable.android.rep
Class RepositoryFactory

java.lang.Object
  net.heroicefforts.viable.android.rep.RepositoryFactory

public class RepositoryFactory
extends Object

A factory class for generating repositories associated with Viable client application. The factory reads through the manifests of the installed applications. Any containing Viable meta-data are prepared for instantiation. This should be considered a heavy object. It is thread-safe.

Concrete repository implementations are expected to implement a public constructor matching the signature ConcreteClass(String, Activity, Bundle).

New repository classes must be registered with Viable by entering a meta-data entry in the Viable's manifest. The key should define the repository type name and the value should specify the fully qualified concrete repository class name.

Client applications may reference repository types with the key "viable-provider" and value matching the repository type name. Other information may be required, but will be specific to the repository implementation.

Author:
jevans
